are-new-frontiers-for-premium-products/amp_articleshow/100819880.cms">Source: Economic Times</a></strong></em></p><p>Everyone has seen the large <em>Soch</em> store in the Forum mall in Koramangala? It sells premium (maybe even designer?) apparel for women, and every time I saw the store I&#8217;d mark it down as a place where I&#8217;d never buy anything because it&#8217;d be too expensive (call it middle class conditioning). </p><p>Where do you think <em>Soch</em> is opening their next few stores?</p><blockquote><p><em>"Soch, another ethnic wear brand, has opened stores in cities like Kurnool, Muzaffarpur, Gorakhpur and Jaipur. It plans to start outlets in Udupi, Dehradun, Allahabad, Madurai, Ludhiana, Barnala, Faridabad, Jodhpur, Vellore and Thrissur, ET has reported"</em></p></blockquote><p><em><strong><a href="https://m.economictimes.com/industry/services/retail/from-vellore-to-barnala-small-towns-are-new-frontiers-for-premium-products/amp_articleshow/100819880.cms">Source: Economic Times</a></strong></em></p><p>And where are big mall developers spending their money?</p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfeb734f-103a-468c-85d8-039c2a11d042_1750x456.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfeb734f-103a-468c-85d8-039c2a11d042_1750x456.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fcfeb734f-103a-468c-85d8-039c2a11d042_1750x456.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q